---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Enam Amevo" currentPage="about">
  <div class="about-page">

    <div class="about-hero">
      <div class="about-photo">
        <img src="/assets/img/headshot.jpg" alt="Enam Amevo" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-intro">
        <h1 class="heading">About Me</h1>
        <p class="about-tagline">"Go beyond the impossible and kick reason to the curb!"<br><span class="quote-attr">— Kamina, Tengen Toppa Gurren Lagann</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-content">

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Who I Am</h2>
        <p>
          I'm Enam Amevo. My name means God's Gift. As the child of Togolese educators and a product of IB schools, I am curious about everything, and want to learn as much as I can.
        </p>
        <p>
         Engineering wasn't the plan at all. I got into film school at LMU, one of the top programs in the country, but could not afford to attend. I still love film deeply, along with manga, psychology, anthropology, history, comic books, etc. Honestly, I just love learning about how people and the world work. I think my love for humanity makes me a good engineer. We should care about how people experience things as our work informs how people experience life. The creativity I pull from storytelling and art directly fuels how I think about design problems. My goal has always been to bring both intellect and creativity to everything I build. I want to build hardware that changes lives.
        </p>
        <p>
         My first exposure to engineering was at Apple's Engineering Technology Camp the summer before my senior year. We learned and worked across a wide range of engineering disciplines, but working with sensors and microcontrollers was my favorite part. When I had to pivot from my film dreams, I knew where to go.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What I Do</h2>
        <p>
          I'm a 3rd year Electrical Engineering student at the Georgia Institute of Technology, with threads in Circuit Technology and Signal Processing.
          I work across the full hardware stack: analog design in Cadence Virtuoso, RTL in Verilog, embedded C, as well as assembly language and real-time DSP on multicore hardware.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Education</h2>
        <div class="edu-card">
          <div class="edu-header">
            <h3>Georgia Institute of Technology</h3>
            <span class="edu-date">Expected December 2027</span>
          </div>
          <p class="edu-degree">B.S. Electrical Engineering</p>
          <p class="edu-details">Threads: Circuit Technology, Signal Processing</p>
          <p class="edu-details">Minor: Materials Science & Engineering</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Skills</h2>
        <div class="about-skills">
          <span class="tag">SystemVerilog/Verilog</span>
          <span class="tag">VHDL</span>
          <span class="tag">C/C++</span>
          <span class="tag">CUDA/MPI</span>
          <span class="tag">MATLAB</span>
          <span class="tag">Cadence/Synopsys</span>
          <span class="tag">PCB Design</span>
          <span class="tag">FPGA</span>
          <span class="tag">Sky130 PDK</span>
          <span class="tag">XMOS</span>
          <span class="tag">Embedded Systems</span>
          <span class="tag">SPICE</span>
          <span class="tag">Python</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What Drives Me</h2>
        <p>
        I want to do real hardware work, that affects peoples daily lives whether they know it or not. Technology that can contribute to better healthcare outcomes and also global sustainabilty efforts. Hardware that can be used to help bridge gaps for the disabled. Chips, circuits, and systems are the invisible infrastructure that make everything else possible.
        </p>
        <p>
        I want to impact the fields of computing, healthcare, energy, and even film and television through electrical engineering. I believe deeply in the intersection of technical skill and creative vision, and I am determined to excel in both.
        </p>
        <p>
        In general, I like to help people so I am also involved on campus! I am the historian for the GTSBE TORCH committee, committee chair for BLIECE (Black, Latino, and Indigenous Students in ECE), and was on the committee for the 2026 IEEE RoboTech Hackathon. I also volunteer as a Peer Instructor at the Hive, Georgia Tech's ECE student-run makerspace!   
        </p>
      </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Connect With Me!</h2>
      <p>
        Feel free to reach out -- I'd love to connect!
      </p>
      <div class="connect-links">
        <p><a href="https://linkedin.com/in/eamevo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></p>
        <p>Email me at <a href="mailto:eamevo3@gatech.edu">eamevo3@gatech.edu</a> with any opportunities!</p>
    </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 40px 80px;
  }

  .about-hero {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 60px;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 4px solid #ffca8a;
  }

  .about-photo {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-photo img {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 4px solid #c2c2c2;
    box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .about-intro .heading {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    display: block;
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about-tagline {
    font-family: 'retro1', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #74808a;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .quote-attr {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #a0a0a0;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .about-content {
    font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
    color: #374054;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #374054;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 3px solid #f0f0f0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-section p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }

  .edu-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 4px solid #c2c2c2;
    box-shadow: 6px 6px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .edu-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .edu-header h3 {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: #374054;
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .edu-date {
    font-family: 'Press Start 2P', cursive;
    font-size: 0.45rem;
    color: #a0a0a0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .edu-degree {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }

  .edu-details {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #74808a;
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }

  .about-skills {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-page { padding: 40px 20px 60px; }
    .about-hero {
      flex-direction: column;
      text-align: center;
      gap: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>